<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1435,1979,2037]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,423]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1979,2004]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
From north 
<collectingCountry box="[457,571,1980,2004]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[587,692,1980,2004]" name="Paraguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[707,792,1980,2004]" name="Bolivia" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[808,879,1980,2004]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and Guianas to 
<collectingCountry box="[1082,1136,1980,2003]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1203,1292,1980,2004]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1409,1980,2004]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it occurs in the states of Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion box="[535,619,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[631,699,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[710,778,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[791,953,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1118,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1130,1278,2013,2037]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="51" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, Pará, 
<collectingRegion box="[306,385,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[398,541,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[554,723,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[735,953,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[966,1135,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1148,1265,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1327,1435,151,175]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
and in the Distrito Federal (
<bibRefCitation author="Reis, N. R. &amp; Peracchi, A. L. &amp; Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P." box="[460,640,185,209]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" refId="ref11214" refString="Reis, N. R., Peracchi, A. L., Pedro, W. A. &amp; Lima, I. P. (2007) Morcegos do Brasil. UEL, Londrina, 253 p." type="book" year="2007">
Reis 
<emphasis box="[518,567,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L." box="[651,811,185,209]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" refId="ref9780" refString="Gardner, A. L. (2008) Mammals of South America. Volume 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats. Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 669 p." type="book" year="2008">Gardner 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,218,243]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Inhabits a large variety of environments such as tropical dry and moist forests, tropical wet forest, subtropical moist and wet forests, and savannas, roosting along rivers, streams, and riparian vegetation of lagoons (
<bibRefCitation author="Mies, R. &amp; Kurta, A. &amp; King, D. G." box="[158,347,290,315]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref10674" refString="Mies, R., Kurta, A. &amp; King, D. G. (1996) Epstesicus furinalis. Mammalian Species, 526, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1996">
Mies 
<emphasis box="[223,273,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Cerrado biome it occurs in both open and forested areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Marinho-Filho, J. &amp; Rodrigues, F. H. G." box="[1082,1381,290,315]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" pagination="266 - 286" refId="ref10580" refString="Marinho-Filho, J., Rodrigues, F. H. G. &amp; Juarez. K. M. (2002) The Cerrado mammals: diversity, ecology, and natural history. In: Oliveira, P. S. &amp; Marquis, R. J., (Eds), The Cerrados of Brazil. Columbia University Press, New York, pp. 266 - 286." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Marinho-Filho 
<emphasis box="[1256,1306,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). We captured 
<specimenCount box="[257,426,326,350]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in a pasture field, near some small buildings near a patch of wooded savanna (
<geoCoordinate degrees="13" direction="south" minutes="46" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" precision="1" seconds="17.03" value="-13.771397">13° 46’ 17.03” S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[263,466,362,386]" degrees="46" direction="west" minutes="37" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" precision="1" seconds="30.44" value="-46.625122">46° 37’ 30.44” W</geoCoordinate>
), in São Domingos, GO.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,423]" box="[199,891,398,423]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,398,423]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" reason="1">Voucher specimens.</emphasis>
Two females – CHUNB 1246 and 1258.
</paragraph>
